WOW! A dream of mine since I was probably 14 years old. It’s hard to put into words how amazing god can be when we do things in good faith, when we are good to others, when we use our richness to help those in need. Thank you to my family and friends for always bringing out the best in me. I am so thankful to have found someone who genuinely cares for me, who appreciates me and who wants to see me grow each day. ✨ Life can teach us so many lessons, and what I’ve learned mostly is that some people come into your life to make you stronger. To my son, YOU DID THAT.. you inspired mommy to fight for her happiness, to be transparent with her feelings and to put herself first. 

Remember to never loose sight of who you are, don’t let anyone manipulate you, or bring you down and if you’re in a situation like that.. look at yourself in the mirror and remember who you are and watch how life unfolds hunny. When you truly learn how to VALUE YOURSELF you begin to act different, everything around you changes for the better. You actually start believing you are worthy of LOVE, RESPECT, SUCCESS, HAPPINESS and all things good. 💜🌷🌸 

Sometimes we learned this things the hard way, then we look back only to see how poorly our sense of value was. I used to be told girls with that attitude of putting our needs and desire first were selfish, and so I never wanted to be that girl, only to find out that’s not true. Loving ourselves is so important, for men and women. How are you going to learn how to love others the right way if you don’t even know how to love yourself first? 

Here’s a few tips how to build up your sense of value:
• Stop comparing yourself to others
• Set boundaries 
• Challenge your negative self talk
• Invest in your health 
• Believe in your capabilities 
• Seek therapy 

Thank you to those who made me feel so powerful & confident during this shoot. I love creating this memories for myself, how do you show self love??

True story: 👇🏽 (Long caption ahead)
There is a chapter of my life I felt so lost and disconnected with whom I was. I had so many ideas and goals but something was holding me back. One day on July of 2021 I decided to surrender and turned my life into Jesus. I had been so far from him and I knew it because my life felt like a mess. Things didn’t actually feel good at the beginning, it was hard, it was painful, I went through many challenges and he tested me and my faith in many ways but I continued to stay strong and reminding him it was his will not mine. Slowly I became so motivated, I gained a strength hard to explained, I had a relationship with the lord, I understood he doesn’t answer our prayers when we want to but when we are ready. 

I started to change for the better, I had a better relationship with the lord, with myself and those around me. I was patient with my process, I started praying for everyone even those who had hurt me and making peace with them as well. I forgave myself and started sharing my story with woman that were going through similar situations. I seriously empathize with anyone feeling lost, depressed or disconnected with life because honestly this life is a true gift we sometimes don’t value enough. 

I have been taking therapy for almost 3 years now, she has been an angel to me and soon I will tell more of my story to help anyone in need. I believe we all have traumas we need to heal from, we all need to be aware of the things that are not good for our soul, and be aware of what we’re been influence about. Be careful who is influencing your life; What tools do they use to confront problems? Are they aggressive? Are they alcoholics? Do they consume drugs? What are they adding into your life?? Ask yourself this questions as well and be honest with your feelings. 🫶🏻

Never be afraid to share your story because you may be able to help someone in need more than you think. We are all humans trying to do better so let’s do that for one another. ✨

I am about to share with you a side of me I haven’t really spoken of before. I hope this can help any woman going through any kind of insecurities know that it all starts when you make the decision to take care of you. 📝✨

I suffer from “ENDOMETRIOSIS” = A chronic disease that causes severe, life-impacting pain during periods, sexual intercourse, abdominal bloating, nausea, fatigue, and sometimes depression, anxiety, weight gain and infertility. Because of this I tend to retained a lot of fluid even after performing surgery to remove endometrial tissues in the areas where it was located. There is no cure for Endometriosis only treatments to control it. I was diagnosed with Endometriosis after getting a tumor removed from my uterus through laparoscopy because otherwise there is no way to truly detect if you suffer from this. 

I had two options .. 1) ignore the situation or 2) take action towards my health. I then began to do research and found that one of the best things for woman with this problem is to exercise daily, avoid certain foods and keep a peaceful life with very lil stress so the disease doesn’t get worst. After more research and so much inflammation and liquid retention I was frustrated and that is how I met @katheryngrau_beauty I found out all the amazing benefits detox massages has and how great it will be for my body and my health. 

My life changed so much ever since I made the decision to love me so much that I would always put my health first. I learned that our bodies is a reflection of how we treat it, our minds play a big role and how we invest in our self care says a lot about our self love. Besides getting my detox massages with Kathy I also performed facial routines to take care of my skin from wearing so much make up constantly. Endometriosis can affect you badly if you don’t control your stress which can lead to acne problems and more but I have been blessed to land in the perfect hands of a woman who cares so much for other peoples well being and she has helped me tremendously throughout my process!! 🥹
